<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08111o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08111o">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08111o"> 111(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> epilepsy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; <i>vel denique, quod fere sancti Patres conformiter ad translationem septuaginta amplectuntur, tremorem quemdam capitis aut etiam omnium membrorum. Ita Bonfrerius, Pererius, alii.</i> <br><font color="green">[... or, finally, since the holy Fathers almost uniformly adopt the translation of the Septuagint, some sort of shaking of the head or even of all his limbs. Thus Bonfrerius, Pererius and others.]</font> <small> Thomas Josephus Lamy, <a name="TJLC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TJLC"><cite title="source">Commentarium in librum geneseos</cite></a> (1884) 256</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
